-4231-b064-3e7b62331aa5%5C%22%3ESkipping%20leadership%20greetings%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22977%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20people%20standing%20in%20an%20elevator%20awkwardly%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6916b72b89026fbb4d0da4aa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221472%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIt's%20never%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20ignore%20senior%20leadership.%3Cp%3ETyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20avoid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-four-consulting-senior-leaders-exodus-leave-for-startups-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esenior%20leaders%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20the%20president%2C%20CEO%2C%20or%20even%20their%20boss's%20boss%26quot%3B%20at%20work%20events%20and%20parties%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEyring%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20instead%20of%20being%20fearful%20of%20saying%20hello%2C%20she%20told%20BI%20that%20guests%20should%20use%20this%20opportunity%20to%20make%20their%20presence%20known%20to%20senior%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20unsure%20of%20what%20to%20say%2C%20try%20referencing%20something%20they've%20shared%20recently%20%E2%80%94%20or%20simply%20thank%20them%20for%20hosting%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2295e2e4ed-cfda-4f1a-8b5a-95d848acc486%5C%22%3ESitting%20out%20on%20the%20fun%20and%20ignoring%20planned%20activities%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20there's%20a%20DJ%20or%20band%2C%20prepare%20to%20get%20up%20and%20dance%2C%20even%20if%20you%20don't%20like%20to%20or%20don't%20think%20you%20are%20good%20at%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Eyring%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIf%20there%20are%20activities%2C%20participate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20this%20is%20your%20opportunity%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F8-simple-ways-to-build-strong-relationships-with-your-coworkers-everyday-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%2