3ESHRM%2C%20which%20has%20been%20embroiled%20in%20controversy%2C%20tried%20to%20exclude%20evidence%20that%20it%20is%20a%20leader%20in%20HR.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20world's%20largest%20human%20resources%20trade%20group%20argued%20that%20the%20plaintiff%20shouldn't%20be%20allowed%20to%20portray%20it%20as%20an%20expert%20in%20HR%20during%20a%20trial%20that%20begins%20with%20jury%20selection%20Monday.%20A%20judge%20disagreed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Society%20for%20Human%20Resource%20Management%2C%20known%20as%20SHRM%2C%20was%20sued%20in%202022%20by%20former%20employee%20Rehab%20Mohamed%2C%20who%20alleges%20that%20she%20faced%20racial%20discrimination%20and%20retaliation%20while%20working%20there%20as%20an%20instructional%20designer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20September%2C%20SHRM%20took%20the%20unconventional%20move%20of%20filing%20a%20motion%20requesting%20that%20the%20federal%20court%20bar%20Mohamed%20from%20introducing%20evidence%20or%20argument%20that%20the%20organization%20is%20a%20specialist%20in%20HR%20best%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoing%20so%20%26quot%3Bwould%20improperly%20hold%20SHRM%20to%20a%20higher%20standard%20than%20any%20other%20employer%20facing%20similar%20claims%2C%20confuse%20the%20issues%2C%20and%20mislead%20the%20jury%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20organization%20argued%20in%20the%20motion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%2C%20US%20District%20Judge%20Gordon%20P.%20Gallagher%20denied%20SHRM's%20request%2C%20saying%20its%20%26quot%3Basserted%20expertise%20in%20human%20resources%20is%20integral%20to%20the%20circumstances%20of%20this%20case%20and%20cannot%20reasonably%20be%20excluded.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20could%20be%20%26quot%3Bvery%20damaging%26quot%3B%20for%20SHRM%20because%20it%20means%20the%20plaintiff%20can%20effectively%20tell%20the%20jury%20that%20the%20trade%20group%20should%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20be%20held%20to%20a%20higher%20standard%20than%20other%20employers%2C%20said%20Betsy%20Bulat%2C%20an%20equity%20partner%20with%20labor%20and%20employment%20firm%20Martenson%2C%20Hasbrouck%2C%20and%20Simon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20makes%20them%20look%20more%20culpable%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20also%20ruled%20that%20the%20Colorado%20jury%20could%20consider%20awarding%20punitive%20damages.%20This%20is%20significant%20as%20it%20means%20that%20if%20the%20jury%20sides%20with%20the%20plaintiff%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere%20could%20be%20a%20huge%20award%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stacey%20Lee%2C%20an%20attorney%20and%20law%20professor%20at%20Johns%20Hopkins%20University's%20Carey%20Business%20School.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESHRM%20has%20consistently%20denied%20Mohamed's%20claims.%20The%20trade%20group%20does%20not%20comment%20on%20litigation%2C%20spokesperson%20Eddie%20Burke%20wrote%20in%20an%20email%20to%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThe%20case%20is%20going%20to%20trial%20because%20SHRM%20has%20a%20longstanding%20practice%20of%20not%20settling%20employment%20cases%20that%20have%20been%20fully%20and%20thoroughly%20investigated%20and%20determined%20to%20be%20meritless%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%20for%20Mohamed%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trial%20is%20set%20to%20begin%20while%20SHRM%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshrm-johnny-taylor-dei-workplace-lawsuits-layoffs-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eembroiled%20in%20various%20controversies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20Business%20Insider%20recently%20reported.%20These%20include%20a%20new%20attendance%20policy%20that%20penalizes%20workers%20who%20arrive%20even%20a%20minute%20after%209%20a.m.%3B%20a%20memo%20about%20a%20%26quot%3Bconservative%26quot%3B%20dress%20code%20that%20bans%20sequins%3B%20and%20a%20companywide%20meeting%20in%20which%20Taylor%20said%20some%20staffers%20were%20%26quot%3Bentitled%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bcomplacent%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bsloppy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20pre-trial%20discovery%2C%20SHRM%20revealed%20the%20existence%20of%20two%20other%20discrimination%20complaints%20from%20employees.%20One%20case%2C%20filed%20with%20the%20Equal%20Employment%20Opportunity%20Commission%20in%202018%2C%20was%20settled.%20The%20other%2C%20filed%20with%20a%20California%20regulator%20in%202021%2C%20is%20pending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESHRM%2C%20which%20claims%20to%20have%20nearly%20340%2C000%20members%2C%20offers%20educational%20materials%20and%20credentialing%20programs%20to%20help%20HR%20professionals%20advance%20in%20their%20careers.%20Mohamed's%20suit%20alleges%20that%20SHRM%20doesn't%20follow%20some%20of%20the%20guidance%20it%20doles%20out%20to%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20the%20judge%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.courtlistener.com%2Fdocket%2F63888588%2F89%2Fmohamed-v-society-for-human-resource-management%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalled%20the%20Mohamed%20case%20%26quot%3Bmessy%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20said%20the%20evidence%20showed%20that%20the%20same%20HR%20person%20tasked%20with%20investigating%20her%20complaints%20was%20also%20ghostwriting%20emails%20for%20Mohamed's%20boss%20and%20drafting%20Mohamed's%20termination%20paperwork%20around%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESHRM's%20industry%20guide%20on%20%26quot%3BHow%20to%20Conduct%20a%20Workplace%20Investigation%2C%26quot%3B%20dated%20about%20two%20weeks%20after%20that%20decision%2C%20said%20investigators%20%26quot%3Bshould%20focus%20on%20being%20impartial%20to%20gather%20and%20consider%20relevant%20facts%20and%20should%20not%20push%20the%20investigation%20in%20any%20particular%20direction.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EAdditional%20reporting%20by%20Jack%20Newsham.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fshrm-discrimination-case-hr-expertise-2025-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1764585901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F692764cc89026fbb4d0e85b9%3Fformat%3D