3Cli%3EMichael%20Stausholm%20bought%20the%20rights%20to%20a%20sustainable%20pencil%20from%20grad%20students%20at%20MIT.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20thought%20the%20pencil%20was%20a%20great%20illustration%20of%20sustainability.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20was%20surprised%20by%20the%20immediate%20commercial%20success.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fmichaelstausholm%2F%3ForiginalSubdomain%3Ddk%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMichael%20Stausholm%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsproutworld.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESproutWorld%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202013%2C%20I%20saw%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fexploding-kittens-kickstarter-card-game%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EKickstarter%20campaign%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20plantable%20pencil.%20Three%20young%20students%20at%20the%20Massachusetts%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20(MIT)%20had%20invented%20the%20pencil%20in%20their%20class.%20The%20idea%20was%20to%20use%20the%20writing%20instrument%2C%20then%20plant%20it%20and%20watch%20herbs%20and%20vegetables%20grow%20from%20seeds%20encased%20in%20the%20pencil.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%20this%20was%20brilliant.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20I%20was%20consulting%20with%20major%20companies%2C%20including%20Nike%20and%20Walmart%2C%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fenvironmental-things-that-dont-help-the-way-you-think-2019-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esustainability%20efforts%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20knew%20people%20had%20a%20really%20hard%20time%20understanding%20what%20sustainability%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20this%20pencil%20was%20a%20perfect%20illustration.%20It%20was%20a%20useful%20item%2C%20made%20from%20all-natural%20materials.%20It%20was%20designed%20with%20the%20end%20in%20mind%3A%20when%20it%20was%20no%20longer%20useful%2C%20users%20could%20quite%20literally%20give%20it%20new%20life.%20I%20wanted%20to%20integrate%20the%20pencil%20into%20my%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22be9fa9bb-ea78-4147-9085-9c6207defc7e%5C%22%3EI%20licensed%20limited%20rights%2C%20and%20then%20bought%20global%20rights%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20students%20and%20licensed%20their%20intellectual%20property%20to%20sell%20the%20pencil%20in%20Denmark%2C%20where%20I%20live.%20Just%20one%20month%20later%2C%20I%20obtained%20the%20rights%20for%20all%20of%20Europe%20and%20started%20my%20company%2C%20SproutWorld.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Michael%20Stausholm%20headshot%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69160cbcabd5e944effaabdb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMichael%20Stausholm%20turned%20down%20Ikea%20to%20protect%20the%20company.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Michael%20Stausholm%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20been%20interested%20in%20the%20Sprout%20pencil%20as%20a%20symbol%2C%20but%20almost%20as%20soon%20as%20I%20began%20selling%20it%2C%20I%20saw%20the%20huge%20commercial%20potential.%20That%20first%20summer%2C%20we%20sold%2050%2C000%20pencils.%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20how%20much%20space%20that%20inventory%20would%20take%20up.%20I%20had%20pencils%20all%20over%20my%20house%2C%20and%20the%20neighborhood%20kids%20were%20helping%20to%20pack%20them%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20year%2C%20I%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmit-student-made-fake-dating-app-prank-harvard-students-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMIT%20students%3C%2Fa%3E%20again%2C%20asking%20to%20purchase%20the%20global%20rights%20for%20the%20pencil.%20They%20were%20robotics%20students%20who%20dreamed%20of%20building%20robots%2C%20not%20pencils.%20I%20can't%20share%20the%20specifics%20of%20the%20deal%2C%20but%20I%20was%20very%20happy%20with%20it%20and%20so%20were%20they%2C%20which%20tells%20me%20it%20was%20fair%20for%20both%20sides.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThirteen%20years%20later%2C%20I%20still%20keep%20in%20touch%20with%20them%2C%20and%20they're%20proud%20of%20how%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fparenting%2Fscience-experiments-for-kids%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eclassroom%20project%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20grown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225567594c-8976-407f-8e9e-22682ddf8282%5C%22%3EI%20was%20ready%20to%20turn%20down%20a%20major%20deal%20to%20project%20the%20brand%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%20schools%20would%20love%20the%20pencils%2C%20but%20I%20realized%20they%20weren't%20viable%20customers%20because%20of%20their%20small%20budgets.%20Soon%2C%20corporations%20began%20reaching%20out%20about%20making%20custom-branded%20pencils.%20That%20side%20of%20the%20business%20flourished.%20Even%20today%2C%20our%20sales%20are%20about%2080%25%20commercial%2C%20and%2020%25%20direct%20to%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20major%20global%20brand%20to%20reach%20out%20to%20me%20was%20Ikea.%20They%20wanted%20about%2050%2C000%20pencils%20for%20an%20anniversary%20celebration%20at%20their%20Italian%20stores.%20There%20was%20just%20one%20problem%3A%20they%20didn't%20want%20the%20SproutWorld%20logo%20on%20the%20pencil%20%E2%80%94%20they%20only%20wanted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fikea-design-history-from-new-museum-2016-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIkea%20branding%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20lived%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftokyo-confidential-bar-bartender-owner-foreigner-challenges-working-living-japan-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworked%20in%20Asia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20understood%20that%20as%20soon%20as%20I%20compromised%20on%20our%20branding%2C%20it%20would%20be%20easier%20for%20other%20companies%20in%20China%20and%20India%20to%20make%20copycat%20pencils.%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%20business%20with%20Ikea%2C%20but%20I%20had%20to%20decline.%20They%20asked%20me%20if%20I%20was%20sure%2C%20and%20I%20said%20yes.%20I%20dared%20to%20say%20no%20to%20a%20corporate%20giant%20in%20order%20to%20protect%20the%20company's%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22760336bd-a82e-4deb-96f2-0d935a859710%5C%22%3EIkea%20came%20back%2C%20and%20we%20later%20made%20branded%20pencils%20for%20Michelle%20Obama%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20couple%20of%20months%20later%2C%20Ikea%20reached%20back%20out%20%E2%80%94%20they%20wanted%20the%20pencils%2C%20and%20were%20willing%20to%20include%20our%20SproutWorld%20branding.%20That%20was%20a%20major%20milestone%20for%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%202018%2C%20an%20agency%20from%20New%20York%20City%20contacted%20me%20about%20using%20the%20pencils%20for%20one%20of%20their%20artists.%20I%20saw%20they%20represented%20major%20musicians%2C%20so%20I%20was%20a%20little%20disappointed%20when%20they%20said%20the%20work%20was%20for%20an%20author.%20However%2C%20we%20then%20obtained%20the%20purchase%20and%20sales%20agreement%2C%20which%20was%20signed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.merchbar.com%2Ftv-shows-movies%2Fmichelle-obama%2Fmichelle-obama-pencil-set%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMichelle%20Obama%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Working%20with%20the%20first%20lady%2C%20with%20her%20emphasis%20on%20healthy%20eating%2C%20was%20a%20perfect%20fit%20for%20our%20brand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20we've%20sold%20more%20than%2085%20million%20Spout%20pencils%20around%20the%20world.%20We%20even%20make%20eyeliner%20pencils.%20Last%20year%2C%20we%20profited%20about%20%241.7%20million%20across%20the%20globe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2284a2127b-cae7-44c4-94d3-b82b57601389%5C%22%3EThe%20symbolism%20of%20the%20pencil%20is%20still%20important%20to%20me%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20thrilled%20with%20the%20commercial%20success%20of%20the%20Sprout%20pencils.%20And%20still%2C%20the%20symbolism%20of%20the%20product%20is%20incredibly%20important%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESustainability%20is%20a%20hard%20concept%20to%20get%20your%20head%20around.%20The%20pencil%20is%20an%20entry%20way%3A%20if%20you%20can%20choose%20a%20sustainable%2C%20all-natural%20pencil%2C%20what%20other%20changes%20can%20you%20make%3F%20No%20one%20can%20be%20100%25%20sustainable%20these%20days%2C%20but%20even%20if%20individuals%20and%20businesses%20change%2020%25%20of%20their%20behavior%2C%20that%20would%20make%20a%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20motto%20is%20%26quot%3Bfrom%20small%20things%2C%20big%20things%20grow.%26quot%3B%20That's%20what%20drives%20us%20as%20a%20company%3A%20inspiring%20global%20change%2C%20one%20pencil%20at%20a%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fturned-student-invention-into-global-eco-friendly-brand-sproutworld-2025-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1764585372000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6916098ee1a9cbb014de24ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fturned-student-invention-into-global-eco-friendly-brand-sproutworld-2025-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Michael%20Stausholm%20turned%20a%20simple%20plantable%20pencil%20into%20SproutWorld%2C%20a%20global%20brand%20inspiring%20sustainability%20one%20small%20idea%20at%20a%20time.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kelly%20Burch)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fturned-student-invention-into-global-eco-friendly-brand-sproutworld-2025-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Aravalli%20row%3A%20Why%20a%20100-metre%20rule%20has%20triggered%20a%20mountain%20of%20concerns%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%